Petropavlovsk Jumps to 4-Week High as Profit Gains on Gold

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-25T15:45:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/petropavlovsk-set-for-four-week-high-as-profit-gains-on-gold.html
Petropavlovsk Plc (POG) , a Russian gold
mining company, climbed to its strongest in four weeks after
posting a first-half profit on higher production and surging
gold prices.  The shares rose 2.9 percent to 808.5 pence by the 4:30 p.m.
close in  London , the highest since July 28.  Net income was $108.2 million, compared with a loss of
$55.4 million a year earlier, London-based Petropavlovsk said
today in a statement. Sales more than doubled to $475.1 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
